rules.description_html:
&lt;!-- SC_OFF --&gt;&lt;div class="md"&gt;&lt;p&gt;No drama-inducing crossposting of content found in other subreddits. Likewise, posts found to direct odious influxes here will be removed. Advertising your fabulous new subreddit is always welcome here.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You are welcome to link to relevant subreddits when warranted, but linking to comment threads is almost always considered drama-inducing regardless of intent. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Relevant AMAs can be linked to. In subreddits smaller than 500k subscribers AMA&amp;#39;s must be posted by a moderator of that subreddit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- SC_ON --&gt;

&lt;!-- SC_OFF --&gt;&lt;div class="md"&gt;&lt;p&gt;We ask that you keep this community awesome by submitting content that is relevant to our experiences as women, for women, or about women. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Several topics are not considered relevant, such as: Medical Advice; Relationship advice; Surveys, Research and Petitions; Horrible things said and done by individuals; Fundraising; Issues affecting men too; Questions for the perspectives of women; Posts made to debate the women of reddit; images outside image guidelines; &amp;quot;PM/chat me&amp;quot;; posts written by AI.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- SC_ON --&gt;

&lt;!-- SC_OFF --&gt;&lt;div class="md"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Post titles should not contain any “trigger” words and flair your post properly. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Users should not be blindsided into words/phrases that affect them negatively. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you do post with either any of these words or phrases, your post will be removed and you’ll have to post it again with a revised title. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- SC_ON --&gt;
